### Key Performance Indicators
- **Alarm Response Metrics**
  - Time to start alarm recording: < 2 seconds
  - Clip creation time: < 5 seconds
  - Evidence package generation: < 30 seconds
  - Stream prioritization latency: < 1 second

- **Analytics Alarm Metrics**
  - False positive rate by analytics type
  - Detection accuracy by camera/zone
  - Processing latency per frame
  - Alarm generation rate

### Standard Video Metrics
- Active streams count by quality/protocol
- Recording storage usage and growth rate
- Analytics processing queue depth
- Stream bandwidth utilization by tenant
- Clip creation frequency and size
- Camera health and uptime
- Storage tier distribution
- API response times

## Alarm-Specific Configuration

```elixir
config :intelitor, Intelitor.Video,
  alarm_response: %{
    pre_alarm_buffer: 30,      # seconds before alarm
    post_alarm_buffer: 300,    # seconds after alarm (5 min)
    alarm_recording_quality: :high,
    alarm_retention_days: 90,  # Extended retention
    evidence_package_format: :mp4,
    
    # Stream prioritization during alarms
    alarm_stream_priority: %{
      critical: [:main_stream, :1080p, 30],
      high: [:main_stream, :720p, 25],
      medium: [:sub_stream, :720p, 15],
      low: [:sub_stream, :480p, 10]
    }
  },
  
  analytics_alarms: %{
    # Cooldown periods to prevent alarm flooding
    cooldown_periods: %{
      motion: 30,        # seconds
      face: 60,
      object: 120,
      behavior: 300,
      crowd: 180
    },
    
    # Zone-specific sensitivity
    zone_sensitivity: %{
      perimeter: 0.6,    # More sensitive
      secure: 0.7,
      public: 0.9,       # Less sensitive
      restricted: 0.5    # Very sensitive
    }
  }
```

## Real-Time Features

### Alarm-Enhanced WebSocket Channels
```elixir
channel "video:alarm:*", Intelitor.Video.AlarmChannel do
  def join("video:alarm:" <> alarm_id, _params, socket) do
    alarm = get_alarm!(alarm_id)
    cameras = get_alarm_cameras(alarm)
    
    # Subscribe to all relevant camera streams
    Enum.each(cameras, fn camera ->
      subscribe_to_stream(camera.id)
    end)
    
    {:ok, %{
      alarm: alarm,
      cameras: serialize_cameras(cameras),
      streams: get_prioritized_streams(cameras, alarm.severity)
    }, socket}
  end
  
  def handle_in("request_evidence", _params, socket) do
    alarm_id = socket.assigns.alarm_id
    {:ok, package} = generate_evidence_package(alarm_id)
    
    push(socket, "evidence_ready", %{
      download_url: package.url,
      expiry: package.expiry,
      size: package.size
    })
    
    {:noreply, socket}
  end
end
```

